OL,3,CWhat counts as cyberflashing and what
OL,4,Cis the punishment?
OL,6,FDefendants found guilty of
OL,7,Fcyberflashing face up to two years in
OL,8,Fprison.
OL,10,FWhat happens to victims?
OL,12,FAll victims who make a police report
OL,13,Frelating to cyberflashing will receive
OL,14,Flifelong anonymity from the point of
OL,15,Fspeaking to authorities.
OL,17,FWhen did cyberflashing become illegal?
OL,19,FIt was made illegal in Scotland in
OL,20,F2010, and was part of the 2023 in
OL,21,FEngland and Wales.
